  "jee_specific": {
    "trap_1": "Relative acceleration = 0, NOT g. Students write a₁₂ = g (forgetting the subtraction). Biggest mistake in this section.",
    "trap_2": "For collision: direction of relative velocity must equal direction of initial separation vector. Many students check speed ratio instead.",
    "trap_3": "Even if launched in opposite directions, collision is possible — direction of u₁₂ is the only thing that matters.",
    "trap_4": "Time of collision: t = d/|u₁₂|, where d is separation along u₁₂ direction — NOT total separation. Students use total separation d directly.",
    "trap_5": "In JEE questions, 'find angle of projection of B for collision' → set up u₁₂ direction = AB direction. One equation in one unknown (θ₂)."
  },
